<br>
The proc weapons proc a LOT less than the epic pet's natural proc.  The epic proc is worthless though in higher level zones due to the pet's low level.<br>
<br>
From reading posts here, it sounds like the 61 air pet is better than both water and epic when the mob is 60+ and you aren't able to let the water pet backstab.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>A pet which is level 60, quads for 80 and has 3500 hps<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I don't know which 61+ pet you are quoting, but I thought I'd offer this.  The 62 water pet is a terrible tank.  It takes very few rounds from a Valor golem to kill it and even with slow it dies quickly without heals.  It also appears to have a low AC.  I went to FG out of boredom (used to live there during luclin) and thought I'd test it out vs the epic pet.  Epic would lose 20-30% health.  The new water pet was consistently losing about 70%.  My guess is his AC stinks.  It looks like the water pet is a true rogue.  High damage from behind, but a poor excuse for a tank.<br>
<br>
I have high hopes for the new earth pet.  Sounds like he has a ton of HPs.  His AC is what worries me most about him.  The root spell will make him not very useful in many groups though.  Now if I could only get my hands on 61 air and BO5. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108671">Varia Darselai</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=graccil>Graccil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 412<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 11:24:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.sonic.net/knightstribunal/misc/graccilsig.gif width=45 height=125 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The epic pet turns light blue at level 62.</span><hr size=1> According to a guildmate with the 65 earth pet, he says the root lands often, and lasts a good while <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8972"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://212.212.159.252/tearaina/imagesP/Graccil.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Garden Gn0ma of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub50.ezboard.com/bgardenofearthlydelights.html">The Garden</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=variathemage>Varia the mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</spa